Package gov.usgs.traveltime

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GenIndex
    This generalized index interface allows computed sample points to be used like they were actual arrays for bilinear interpolation.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AllBrnRef
    Umbrella storage for all non-volatile travel-time data.
    AllBrnVol
    Umbrella storage for all volatile branch level travel-time data.
    ArrComp
    Comparator to sort travel-time results into ascending arrival time order
    AuxTtRef
    Auxiliary data augmenting the basic travel-times.
    BrnDataRef
    Store all non-volatile information associated with one travel-time branch.
    BrnDataVol
    Generate all volatile information associated with one travel-time branch.
    CWBProperties
    Static classes related to properties.
    Decimate
    Decimation methods used at various places in the travel-time package are implemented here.
    Ellip
    Implements the Dziewonski & Gilbert ellipticity correction algorithm for one phase.
    EllipDels
    Virtual array of ellipticity correction sample distances.
    EllipDeps
    Virtual array of ellipticity correction sample depths.
    ExtraPhases
    Provides a programmatic way of getting information about diffracted and add-on phases.
    ModConvert
    Earth model dependent unit conversions and constants.
    ModDataRef
    Store Earth model data for one wave type.
    ModDataVol
    Store Earth model data for one wave type.
    PhGroup
    Holds one phase group.
    ReadTau
    Read the FORTRAN generated travel-time files.
    Spline
    A collection of spline interpolation routines needed for the computation of travel times.
    TauInt
    Integrate tau and distance, x, along a ray path through the normalized, flattened Earth model.
    TauUtil
    Utility methods for the travel-time package.
    Topography
    Handle corrections for reflections from the free surface.
    TopoLats
    Virtual array of topographic sample latitudes.
    TopoLons
    Virtual array of topographic sample longitudes.
    TtFlags
    Organize all the auxiliary travel-time information by phase.
    TTime
    This class contains complete information (including auxiliary information) for all phases generated by a source at the desired depth and source receiver-distance.
    TTimeData
    Holds everything known about one seismic phase at a particular source depth and source-receiver distance.
    TtMain
    Sample driver for the travel-time package.
    TtResult
    Results of a travel-time calculation.
    TtStat
    Holds a set of observed travel-time statistics for one phase.
    TtStatLinFit
    Acquire the travel-time statistics data in one degree bins, do the linear fits between the break flags, and release the raw statistics data.
    TtStatSeg
    Holds one travel-time statistics linear interpolation segment for one statistics variable.
    UpDataRef
    Store non-volatile up-going branch data for one wave type.
    UpDataVol
    Store volatile up-going branch data for one wave type.
